Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: emu10k1: Fix out of bounds access in snd_emu10k1_pcm_channel_alloc()
Git-commit: d29f59051d3a07b81281b2df2b8c9dfe4716067f
Patch-mainline: v6.0-rc5
References: git-fixes CVE-2022-48702 bsc#1223923

The voice allocator sometimes begins allocating from near the end of the
array and then wraps around, however snd_emu10k1_pcm_channel_alloc()
accesses the newly allocated voices as if it never wrapped around.

This results in out of bounds access if the first voice has a high enough
index so that first_voice + requested_voice_count > NUM_G (64).
The more voices are requested, the more likely it is for this to occur.

This was initially discovered using PipeWire, however it can be reproduced
by calling aplay multiple times with 16 channels:
aplay -r 48000 -D plughw:CARD=Live,DEV=3 -c 16 /dev/zero

